  "text": "The first equation (Decomposition One) describes the incomplete decomposition of Al(OH) 3 (s) to Al 2 O 3 (s) and water vapor, H 2 O (g). As a consequence of the incomplete (or non-stoichiometric) dehydroxylation of the gibbsite, Al(OH) [CITATION_1] , a certain amount of boehmite, AlO(OH) (s) is formed. Thus, one would expect a low value for the calculation of gibbsite content if one were to apply the theoretical \"G\" value of this mass loss event.",
